Is it possible for the child process to interfere with global THP settings
during an abnormal exit?

The fork() call creates a child process that inherits these signal handlers.
Because the child uses PR_SET_PDEATHSIG to receive SIGTERM when the parent
terminates, an abnormal parent exit will cause the child to catch the
signal and also invoke thp_restore_settings().

This redundant restoration by the child could race with the parent or with
the execution of the next test in the suite. Resetting the signal handlers
in the child immediately after forking would prevent this.

